HEADWORD: Cantoral
<hw>Can"tor*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or belonging to
a cantor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cantoral staff</b></col>, <cd>the official staff or baton
of a cantor or precentor, with which time is marked for the
singers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

